<?style?>
.aufbau-section { padding-top: 2rem; }
.aufbau {
    max-width: 80rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
}
.aufbau-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
}
.aufbau-name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    line-height: 1;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}
.aufbau-tag {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    max-width: 40rem;
}
.aufbau-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
}
.aufbau-prose p {
    color: var(--text-default);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
}
.aufbau-prose .highlight { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
.aufbau-prose strong { color: var(--text-heading); }
.aufbau-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
}
.aufbau-links a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
}
.aufbau-links a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }
.aufbau-links .meta { color: var(--text-muted); }
.aufbau-code {
    background: #111827;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
}
.aufbau-code pre { margin: 0; }
.aufbau-code code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #e5e7eb;
    white-space: pre;
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
}
.aufbau-code .c { color: #6b7280; }
.aufbau-code .k { color: #c4b5fd; }
.aufbau-install {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
}
@media (max-width: 860px) {
    .aufbau-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
    .aufbau-name { font-size: 2.25rem; }
}
<?/style?>

<?use id="hero-cmp"?>
    <?label?>Dynamic Formal Systems<?/label?>
    <?title?>Truth by <span class="highlight">construction</span><?/title?>
    <?description?>The DFS lab is the main research division at Unusupicious. We bridge formal constructions of the world and it's physical substrate. Trying to close the gap between logic and the unsayable. <?/description?>
</?use?>

<section class="section aufbau-section">
    <div class="aufbau">
        <p class="aufbau-eyebrow">Main developppement product</p>
        <h2 class="aufbau-name">AUFBAU</h2>
        <p class="aufbau-tag">A typed prefix-parsing engine for constrained decoding.</p>

        <div class="aufbau-grid">
            <div class="aufbau-prose">
                <p>The systems is named after Carnap's <em>Der logische Aufbau der Welt</em>. In the same way he tried to built the whole world on a rather small set of construction rules, AUFBAU makes the wager that LLMs guided by a correct-by-construction constraint layer.  From a dynamically loaded typed grammar it constructs, token by token, only the continuations that keep a partial syntax tree <span class="highlight">well-formed and well-typed</span>.</p>
                <p>In the technical sense, its a prefix parser for a subset of attribute grammars. </p>
                <p>The model interface lives in <strong>Proposition 7</strong>, where we use an <em> oracle </em> interface in the generation loop that allows us to verify if a token is a valid continuation of the current input. Validity is not only syntactic derivability but also semantic correctess.</p>
                <div class="aufbau-links">
                    <a href="https://github.com/Unsuspicious-Industries/aufbau" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
                    <a href="https://pypi.org/project/aufbau-rs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PyPI</a>
                    <span class="meta">Rust core · Python bindings (PyO3) · MIT</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <div class="aufbau-code" style="margin-top: -4rem;"><pre>
                <code>

Variable(var) ::= Identifier[x]
BaseType ::= Identifier | '(' Type ')'
AtomicType ::= BaseType | '(' Type ')'
FunctionType ::= AtomicType '->' Type
Type ::= AtomicType | FunctionType
Lambda(lambda) ::= 'λ' Identifier[a] ':' Type[τ] '.' Expression[e]
AtomicExpression ::= Variable | '(' Expression ')' | Lambda
Application(app) ::= Expression[l] AtomicExpression[r]
Expression ::= AtomicExpression |  Application

x ∈ Γ
----------- (var)
Γ(x)

Γ[a:τ] ⊢ e : ?B
--------------------------- (lambda)
τ → ?B

Γ ⊢ l : ?A → ?B, Γ ⊢ r : ?A
--------------------------------- (app)
?B
                </code></pre></div>
                <p class="aufbau-install">AUFBAU grammar file format. Install with <code>pip install aufbau-rs</code> and get started with your own grammar files.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

